This survey may get to this, but I have two complaints.  I've raised both issues with customer service and have received no satisfaction.   First, we have several accounts and have banked with <THIS BK> for many years.  We like your customer service and the convenience of the proximity to our local branch.  That said, it seems excessive to charge me $4 per account per month as a maintenance fee.    Secondly, with your upgrade to a new system recently, I receive multiple emails each day informing me of a remote login that seem to all be from USAA, where I set up on their app to give me account balance information for my <THIS BK> accounts.  Their app is convenient and is a quick and an easy place for me to get a quick snapshot of accounts at both institutions.  Because of the way it happens (as explained to me), <THIS BK> systems don't recognize the source of the query and immediately sends me an email warning me of potential fraud, which is good, except that I receive too many emails/messages already and these are basically nuisance messages that I have come to ignore and defeats the purpose of the message altogether.  The result is that I'm ignoring ALL messages from <THIS BK> that seem to fit this mold.  On these two issues, we are looking for other banking options that fit our needs and address these two issues specifically.
